ZH: 血管是人体内输送血液的管道。
EN: Blood vessels are the pipelines that transport blood inside the body.

ZH: 脑部有丰富的血管分布。
EN: The brain has a rich distribution of blood vessels.

ZH: 糖尿病会损害血管。
EN: Diabetes can damage blood vessels.

ZH: 血管堵塞可能导致心脏问题。
EN: Blockage of blood vessels can lead to heart problems.

ZH: 高血压会增加血管破裂的风险。
EN: Hypertension increases the risk of blood vessel rupture.

ZH: 饮食习惯可以影响血管健康。
EN: Dietary habits can influence the health of blood vessels.

ZH: 运动可以促进血管的弹性。
EN: Exercise can promote the elasticity of blood vessels.

ZH: 饮酒过量会损伤血管。
EN: Excessive drinking can damage blood vessels.

ZH: 血管扩张可以增加血流量。
EN: Blood vessel dilation can increase blood flow.

ZH: 血管炎是指血管壁发炎。
EN: Vasculitis refers to inflammation of blood vessel walls.

ZH: 血管狭窄会导致血压升高。
EN: Narrowing of blood vessels can lead to high blood pressure.

ZH: 血栓形成可以堵塞血管。
EN: Blood clot formation can block blood vessels.

ZH: 脂肪堆积会影响血管通畅。
EN: Accumulation of fat can affect blood vessel patency.

ZH: 冷水浸泡可以收缩血管。
EN: Immersion in cold water can constrict blood vessels.

ZH: 血管脆弱容易破裂。
EN: Fragile blood vessels are prone to rupture.

ZH: 年老者的血管弹性较差。
EN: The elasticity of blood vessels diminishes with age.

ZH: 血管损伤会引起出血。
EN: Blood vessel injury can cause bleeding.

ZH: 炎症会使血管壁增厚。
EN: Inflammation can thicken blood vessel walls.

ZH: 血管内皮细胞具有保护作用。
EN: Endothelial cells in blood vessels have a protective function.
